                   <div class="uiScroller forceScroller" id="panelScroller" data-scroller='{"enableRefresh":"true"}'>              
                    
                        
                     <div data-role="page" id="centerMain" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-family:DINProFont;background-image: url({!HostURL}{!URLFOR($Resource.FA_Images, 'FA_Background_Image_for_Four_Acres.jpg')});background-repeat:repeat-x; background-size: 100%;">
                            <div data-role="header" style="font-family:DINProFont;">
                                <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Help </h1>
                            </div><!-- /header-->
                           
                                               
                            <div data-role="content" style="padding: 40px;font-family:DINProFont;background-color: #ffffff;border-radius: 9px 9px 9px 9px;margin-top: 40px;margin-left: 30px;margin-right: 30px;margin-bottom: 40px;border-style:solid;border-width:2px;border-color: #006699;"> 
                            
                               
                                 <a href="/apex/Chatter#page=groups&group={!$Label.FA_Help_GroupID}" target="_self" data-role="button" data-theme="e" data-icon="gear" style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:18px">Collaborate on Four Acres Help</a>                            
                                        
                                          <div data-role="collapsible-set" style="background:#ffffff;font-family:DINProFont;">
                                          <div data-role="collapsible" data-theme="b" style="font-family:DINProFont;"  >
                                          <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">The Functionality of Venues tab in the Four Acres App</h1>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Venues Section in the Four Acres App will give the information of the Leadership Venues of the Unilever Four Acres available across the globe. By Selecting on each of any available venue, all the necessary details related to that particular venue will be displayed like View Map, Facilities, Travel info and City Detour.  </p>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">The view will be like </p>
                                         <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_CentreCollapsedImage}" width="800" height="500"/>
                                          <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">View Map</h4>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">On Click on the View Map and any other section available, displays as below</p>
                                          <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_Image_View_Map}" width="800" height="500"/>
                                          <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Facilities @ Four Acres:  </h4>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Gives the details of the Services and IT activities available at that venue. Gives the general information of the meeting rooms, Wifi Facilities and Other Technical Support.</p>
                                          <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Travel Info:  </h4>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Gives the information related to Transportation services</p>
                                          <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">City Detour:  </h4>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Gives the general information of the City and places to be visited with images  </p>
                                          </div>
                                          
                                         <div data-role="collapsible" data-theme="b" style="background:#ffffff;font-family:DINProFont;">
                                         <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Features available in the Course Chatter Section</h1>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">In the Course Chatter section, User can view the feeds related to the registered courses and can interact with the instructor and audience of that particular training. Participant will be able to view the feeds posted before .during and after the course.There is also feature where participant interacts with Instructor and admin for doing pre-work assessment assigned as part of the training programme</p>

                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">My Chatter</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Will display all the related to User Followed and groups</p>
                                                                                 
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">All Four Acres</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">This section will be helpful for the participant to share post and Read post across all the four acres member.</p>
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Groups</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">The participant will be able to view all the groups of the training registered and by selecting each group he can interact with the members of that particular group</p>
                                         <p style="text-align:centre">
                                         <apex:image id="groups" value="{!$Label.FA_Help_ChatterGroupsImage}" width="800" height="500"/>
                                         </p>
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">People</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Participant can view the fellow members whom he/she was following and his/her followers</p>
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Four Acres Help</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Four Acres Help is a private group and the participant can only read the information about any updates related to the course occurrences posted by the admin</p>
                                         </div>
                                         
                                         
                                         
                                         <div data-role="collapsible" data-theme="b" style="background:#ffffff;font-family:DINProFont;">
                                         <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Programme section  in the Chatter</h1>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Programme section displays all the Completed courses of the participant and all the Upcoming training for which he was registered. In this the overview of the training program, Schedule and Training venue will be displayed for the participant</p>
                                         <p style="text-align:centre">
                                         <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_ProgrammesImage}" width="800" height="500"/>
                                         </p>
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Upcoming Programmes</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">This page is available to view the necessary trainings that need to be attended by the participant in the coming days. Participant will know at what days he training was scheduled well in advance so that any planned activities will be planned</p>
                                         
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Completed Programmes</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">This page gives the entire content of courses he was registered past and attended. Participant can check all the relevant overview of the courses he attended past.</p>
                                         
                                         <h4 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Programme Logistics:</h4>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Please click on the Programme Logistics,Select the course and give the Programme Logistics required in the below screen. Here the participant’s arrival date, departure date and other details including the dietary Programme Logistics and other requirements(if any) as mentioned below will be entered by the participant and click on Update button.</p>
                                         <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_ProgPrefImage}" width="800" height="500"/>
                                         </div>
                                         
                                         
                                         <div data-role="collapsible" data-theme="b" style="background:#ffffff;font-family:DINProFont;" >
                                         <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Details available for the User in My Schedule </h1>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">My Schedule will display the training dates of the Upcoming courses and also the completed courses in either on Monthly or Weekly or Daily.<br/> He can also view the short description of the course by clicking the mouse on the training event in the calendar.If Participant selects the month, it displays all the training events of the participant for the current month and he/she can also view the previous months training calendar also by clicking on the previous arrow button.<br/> For knowing the Upcoming events he/she can view by clicking the Next arrow button.If the Participant selected the week button on the calendar page, the page displays the current week of the year and can view any courses registered in that week.Left and Right arrow buttons are available to view the past weeks and future week to check at what dates, the particular participant has been enrolled for the training programmes.<br/>If the participant selects the day button ,then the page displays the current day view and can navigate to other dates using the left and right arrow controls.</p>                              
                                         <p style="text-align:centre">
                                         <apex:image id="calender" value="{!$Label.FA_Help_CalenderImage}" width="750" height="500"/>
                                         </p>
                                         </div>
                                         
                                         <div data-role="collapsible" data-theme="b" style="background:#ffffff;font-family:DINProFont;" >
                                         <h1 style="font-family:DINProFont;">Functionality of Feedback Section</h1>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Feedback screen helps the participant to give the feedback on the courses attended. The section displays only the courses for which he needs to submit the feedback. The participant will select the course from the “Choose One” section and gives his feedback on the course for which they have attended and request for feedback pending.</p>
                                         <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_FeedbackImage}" width="800" height="400"/>
                                         <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">On clicking the “Give Feedback” the below screen appears</p>
                                         <apex:image value="{!$Label.FA_Help_FBDetailimage}" width="800" height="600"/>
                                          <p style="font-family:DINProFont;font-size:16px;">Here there are different sections with relevant questionnaire where the participant will be giving the Ratings in the drop down button and if any comments need to be addressed, it will be texted in the comments Textbox. Once give the Click on the Submit button to send feedback on the course attended</p>
                                          </div>
                                               
                                                                               
                                        </div>                      
                            </div><!-- /content -->
                            
                            <br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    </div><!-- /page -->
                    
                    
                    
